If you want to test this on Ubuntu or Debian, you can install this application first:
module-assistant


1. build sys_reg and dram modules and install them.
2. load modules into kernel.
3. mknod /dev/phy_mem c 85 0
4. compile fileview and mem_map
5. run mem_map and do not exit.
5. run fileview /dev/phy_mem




Copied from: http://ilinuxkernel.com/?p=1303, with minor modifications.


Please note that totalram_pages only represent all physical RAM pages, it does not include PCI addresses.
